# BeagleBone — Sensor Server

Central TCP server that receives sensor state from the ESP32-Hub and exposes it to the data controller.

## Source Files

| File | Description |
|:-----|:------------|
| `sensor_server.c` | Main TCP server, JSON parsing, sensor state management |
| `sensor-server-wrapper.sh` | systemd wrapper script |

## Dependencies

```bash
sudo apt install libjson-c-dev:armhf
```

## Build

```bash
cd beaglebone/server
export ARCH=arm
export CROSS_COMPILE=arm-linux-gnueabihf-
${CROSS_COMPILE}gcc sensor_server.c -o sensor_server -ljson-c

# Verify architecture
file sensor_server
# Expected: ELF 32-bit LSB pie executable, ARM...
```

## Deploy

```bash
scp sensor_server debian@beaglebone.local:/home/debian/controller/
ssh debian@beaglebone.local "sudo systemctl restart sensor-server data-controller && sudo systemctl status sensor-server"
```

